## 8. Map Configuration & Building Metadata 🧱

### 8.1 `MAP_CONFIG`

File: `frontend/lib/map/config.ts`

Defines foundational map behavior:

- `center`: `[-96.7025, 40.8202]` — near Kauffman Residential Center
- `defaultZoom`: 15.5 — high-level campus view
- `buildingZoom`: 17.5 — zoom level for building-focused views
- `minZoom` / `maxZoom`: 13–20 — restricts zoom extremes
- `pitch`: 60 — 3D perspective angle
- `bearing`: -15 — subtle rotation for cinematic framing
- `style`: `mapbox://styles/mapbox/dark-v11` — modern dark theme
- `transitionDuration`: 1500 — smooth camera transitions

### 8.2 `CAMPUS_BOUNDS`

Also in `frontend/lib/map/config.ts`:

- Encodes the **minimal rectangular extent** that fully encompasses all geolocated course sections in `parsed_sections.json`.
- Used by:
  - The React Map `maxBounds` prop
  - The Mapbox `within` filter for 3D building extrusion

### 8.3 `BUILDINGS` Metadata

File: `frontend/lib/map/buildings.ts`

Defines curated building objects:

- `id`, `name`, `shortName`
- `type`: e.g., `residential`, `academic`, `dining`, `library`, `athletic`, `recreation`, `administrative`
- `coordinates`: `[lng, lat]` for center points
- `capacity`: approximate capacity
- `hours`: textual hours of operation
- `description`: short functional narrative
- `polygon`: approximate footprint polygon for building overlays

This metadata powers:

- Building selection and display
- Type-based color coding
- Enhanced storytelling in overlays and panels

